shared_text:
Grove City Area High School
July 3 at 7:24 AM ·

Modification to our RTP Plan -
The use of masks for the GCASD off season workout and conditioning plan is being modified due to the Pennsylvania Department of Health and Governor Wolf's announcement on July 1. To comply with the new state requirements for wearing masks when in public, all student athletes and coaches are required to wear a mask while on school property and NOT directly engaged in physical activity. Coaches are permitted to remove their masks when speaking/coaching at a distance that maintains social distancing guidelines. It is the responsibility of the head coach for each team to communicate this change to all participating off season workout athletes and to require all program participants to comply.

Coaches are permitted to remove their masks when speaking/coaching at a distance that maintains social distancing guidelines. It is the responsibility of the head coach for each team to communicate this change to all participating off season workout athletes and to require all program participants to comply.

post_text:
Happy National School Nurse Day! GCASD would like to thank all of the wonderful nurses we are blessed to have at our school district. The compassion, ability, and sheer brilliance of the School Nurse is a great comfort to all parents. They are available all hours of the school day and know how best to care for the students. School Nurses take the time to diminish anxieties, educate teachers and staff of students health concerns and plan for emergencies.

We applaud your work, dedication, and selfless commitment to your students. Thank you! 💛🖤 #GCASDproud

post_text:
GCASD Cafe will be offering free breakfast and lunch meals for students that qualify for our free & reduced school meals program. Our first distribution of
meals will be Friday March 20th. If your child(ren) has already qualified, you will be receiving more information later today on how to receive your meals. If you have not previously applied and qualified for free & reduced school meals, and your family is experiencing a hardship during this time, please go online to www.schoolcafe.com to apply. You will need your child(ren)'s student ID number. You will create a username and password. Please have the gross income of each family member living in the household ready to provide in the application. Once your application is processed, you will be notified of the determination of your application. If you are in immediate need of food, please contact the Grove City Food Pantry @ 724.458.5208.

GCMS would like to invite you to the 31st annual GCMS Spaghetti Dinner.

Each year GCMS teachers and staff prepare the food and cheerfully serve it to hundreds of community and student customers.

This year's dinner will take place on Friday February 7, 2020 in the middle school cafeteria from 4-7 pm.

Cost is $8.00 for adults $5.00 for students $5.00 for Seniors

All money raised will go back into student self-esteem projects here at Grove City Middle School.

We look forward to seeing you this Friday! #GCASDproud
